    'select_a_status_that_best_describes_this_budget'                                                                                                                 => 'fr_Select a status that best describes this budget:<br><br>(1) <b>indicative</b> - a non-binding estimate for the described budget.<br><br>(2) <b>committed</b> - a binding agreement for the described budget.<br><br>If no status is selected, the budget is assumed to be indicative.',
    'if_you_are_reporting_both_programmes'                                                                                                                            => 'fr_If you are reporting both programmes (parent activities) and projects (child activities), choose the hierarchical level that most of your activities are at - e.g. parent activity = 1; child activity = 2. <br>If all your activities are at the same level i.e. you have no child activities, then choose 1.',
    'add_a_humanitarian_flag_to_every_activity'                                                                                                                       => 'fr_Add a \'Humanitarian Flag\' to every activity that your organisation publishes data on. Selecting "Yes" means that your activities are wholly or partially addressing a humanitarian crisis. You can add or remove the flag from individual activities if required later.',
    'each_element_represents_a_basic_unit_of_information_in_the_iati_standard'                                                                                        => 'fr_Each data \'element\' is a piece of information in the IATI Standard about your organisation or activities. Click on each element below and complete the fields in the data entry form to add information. You can access guidance by clicking on the \'?\' icons.',
    'the_type_of_finance_eg_grant_loan'                                                                                                                               => 'fr_The type of finance that best applies to your activities - e.g. a grant or loan. This default will be applied to all of your activities. It can be overridden for individual activities or transactions if needed. <br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/financetype/\'>Click here for more information</a>',
    'you_can_select_regions_from_the_oecd_dac_un_or_your_own_internal_codelist'                                                                                       => 'fr_You can select regions from the \'OECD DAC\', \'UN\' or your own internal codelist. IATI recommends that you use the \'OECD DAC\' codelist. If you do not choose an option, then the codelist \'OECD DAC\' is assumed.<br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/regionvocabulary/\'>Click here for more information on these codelists</a>.',
    'enter_the_organisations_iati_organisation_identifier'                                                                                                            => 'fr_Enter the organisation\'s IATI organisation identifier. If you cannot provide an identifier then you must provide the name of the organisation.<br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/guidance/publishing-data/data-quality-and-visualisation/finding-other-organisations-identifiers/\'>Click here for information on how to find other organisations\' identifiers</a>.',
    'the_type_of_aid_being_supplied_project_type_intervention'                                                                                                        => 'fr_The type of aid being supplied (project-type intervention, budget support, debt relief, etc.). This default will be applied to all new activities. It can be overridden for individual activities if needed. <br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/aidtype/\'>Click here for more information</a>',
    'what_is_an_activity_description'                                                                                                                                 => 'fr_For IATI, you provide information on your organisation\'s development and humanitarian \'activities\'. Activities can be programmes, projects, or any unit of work that makes sense for your organisation.',
    'missing'                                                                                                                                                         => 'fr_Not entered',
