    'this_will_create_an_admin_account_for_you_as_an_individual'                                                                                                      => 'fr_This will create an admin account for you as an individual',
    'flow_type_is_a_way_to_categorise'                                                                                                                                => 'fr_Flow type is a way to categorise financial flows. It distinguishes between official development assistance (ODA), other official flows (OOF), or several types of private flows. This default will be applied to all of your activities. It can be overridden for individual activities or transactions if needed.<br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/flowtype/\'>Click here for more information</a>',
    'whether_the_aid_is_untied_tied_or_partially_tied'                                                                                                                => 'fr_Whether funding is untied, tied, or partially tied. Tied funding must be spent on goods or services procured from a particular country or group of countries. This default will be applied to all of your activities. It can be overridden for individual activities or transactions if needed.<br><br><a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/tiedstatus/\'>Click here for more information</a>',
    'this_is_the_unique_id_for_your_organisation'                                                                                                                     => 'fr_This is the unique ID for your organisation that you entered when you set up your IATI Registry account. It is usually an abbreviation of your organisation\'s name.',
    'the_api_token_is_a_unique_key_that_is_generated_from_your_organisation'                                                                                          => 'fr_This is a unique key which gives IATI Publisher permission to add data to the IATI Registry on your behalf. Generate a token in the \'My Account\' tab after <a href=\'https://www.iatiregistry.org/user/login\' target=\'_blank\'>logging in to the IATI Registry</a>.',
    'enter_api_token_here'                                                                                                                                            => 'fr_Enter API token here',
